results.name: Number of nonisomorphic generalized Petersen P(n,k) graphs on 2n nodes for 1<=k<=floor((n-1)/2).
comment: A generalized Petersen graph P(n,k) has 2n nodes and 3n edges and consists of an outer n-gon and an inner {n,k} star polygon for some k in the range 1<=k<=floor((n-1)/2); sequence gives number of nonisomorphic generalized Petersen graphs P(n,k) (for any k).
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Generalized Petersen Graph
example: The generalized Petersen graphs P(22,k) for k = 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 10 are pairwise nonisomorphic, so a(22) = 8. - Arjana Zitnik (Arjana.Zitnik(AT)fmf.uni-lj.si)
mathematica: CountDistinct /@ Table[CanonicalGraph[PetersenGraph[n, k]], {n, 3, 79}, {k, (n - 1)/2}] (* _Eric W. Weisstein_, May 13 2017 *)
